  <div class="comment-content">

    <div class="edit-comment-hide">
      <div class="comment-body markdown-body markdown-format js-comment-body">
          <p><em>From <a href="https://code.google.com/u/jjbross@gmail.com/">jjbross@gmail.com</a> on December 28, 2011 14:02:41</em></p>

<p>the mapfile writer now supports a parameter "language-preference" which takes an ISO 3166-1 string ( <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1_alpha-2">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1_alpha-2</a> ) as value. For example, setting language-preference=en lets the writer prefer English names of entities. If no name in the preferred language exists the original name is chosen.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

  </div>
